
1.Download
==========

- visit the website : https://www.boost.org/users/download/

- for ubuntu users  : $sudo apt-get install libboost-test-dev
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________

2.Usage variants
================

2.1.Single-header usage variant
you prefer to avoid the compilation of standalone library
|---------------------------------------------|
|#include <boost/test/included/unit_test.hpp> |
|---------------------------------------------|

2.2.Static library usage variant
For most users, who has an access to pre-built static library
|------------------------------------|
|#include <boost/test/unit_test.hpp> |
|------------------------------------|

2.3.Shared library usage variant
Link test module dynamically with the Unit Test Framework built as a shared library.
|------------------------------------|
|#define BOOST_TEST_DYN_LINK         |
|#include <boost/test/unit_test.hpp> |
|------------------------------------|
_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________

3.Documentation
================
- visit the website : https://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_58_0/libs/test/doc/html/index.html

